{"id": "1504828501000327268", "channel_id": "1504828501000327268", "type": 0, "author_id": "217131427693723664", "author_name": "aaa_wawasabi", "author_bot": false, "content": "UGC contests should help foster a creative community, but there are several recurring organizational issues that continue to reduce motivation and frustrate participants in the following areas:\n\n1. *Deadline and Announcement Enforcement*\nDeadlines are often not strictly respected, which is unfair to those who finish on time. In addition, winner announcement dates are not specified. The v2.4.1 contest took nearly two months to announce results. A clear, guaranteed timeline is needed to reduce uncertainty.\n\n2. *Transparency in Judging Criteria*\nThere was significant disappointment (in non-EN communities) during the v2.4.1 contest because expectations and the final judging results were not aligned. Although v2.4.3 made the judging criteria public, the process itself is still lacking. To build trust, I suggest adding \"Judge’s Choice\" blurbs alongside the winners. Explaining what made an entry stand out would clarify expectations for future participants.\n\n3. *Poor Alignment With Game Versions*\nSkipping versions (e.g., v2.4.1 to v2.4.3) is problematic for time-sensitive content like guides. Creators may hesitate to begin or finish content because the schedule feels unpredictable. Aligning contests with major version cycles instead (2.5.x, 2.6.x) is better than running too many smaller events without sufficient resources.\n\n4. *Lack of a Proper Submission/File System*\nThe current reliance on social media tags and manual links is prone to error and confusion. Links often break during long judging periods. Some users miss contests entirely by assuming tags alone count as submission. A centralized submission portal would ensure no entries are lost.\n\n5. *Limited Winner Showcase*\nWinner announcements are currently presented as a static PNG containing usernames only. The archive of submissions and winners is hidden inside a long Google document that many users will never fully browse. Artworks, guides, and miscellaneous works deserve easier visibility and preservation.", "timestamp": "2026-05-15T12:51:13+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👆", "emoji_id": null, "count": 7}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1504828501000327268", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "UGC Contests need better structure and transparency", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361169005435420785"], "is_thread_starter": true}
{"id": "1504831314535256074", "channel_id": "1504828501000327268", "type": 0, "author_id": "452731110556696596", "author_name": "aurora3981", "author_bot": false, "content": "I want to add to 4. The submission process should include a way to contact in case any errors occur with the submission.", "timestamp": "2026-05-15T13:02:23.799000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 4}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1504828501000327268", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "UGC Contests need better structure and transparency", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361169005435420785"]}
