{"id": "1504830539763552276", "channel_id": "1504799287853322375", "type": 0, "author_id": "480803690140270592", "author_name": "zod.444", "author_bot": false, "content": "<:point:1356053112292511815>", "timestamp": "2026-05-15T12:59:19.079000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1504799287853322375", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Ramona skin", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361169005435420785"]}
{"id": "1504798331593818263", "channel_id": "1504798331593818263", "type": 0, "author_id": "1060975277531992145", "author_name": "arandomflamev2", "author_bot": false, "content": "As it is presented the new realm is very anti-synergistic with almost every unit that came before.\n200 embryo bar makes every skill that gains embryo fusion worse, and the passive gain of fusion isn't big enough.\nThe absence of first devour removes the biggest defensive mechanism that Caro has.\nPropagation Caro is supposed to be a realm that buffs exalts, but with how embryos are harder to gain, it will be harder to try to make use of embryos as aliemus batteries, and the exalt effects are not going to be strong enough to replace the shield and temporary strength gained when a first devour triggers.\n\nThis is not a post about Saya being bad. She is a good-maybe even great character and she works with Propagation Caro. But i am afraid of the implementation of future units with Propagation Caro, because if they are balanced around how this realm variation works, it will still make every unit before them a lot harder to play, in both survivability and the actual ability to exalt consistently.\nNone of the other realms before caro had this problem, no aequor or ultra unit was hindered by the new realm variation, most even benefited greatly from it. But that is not the case with caro characters. That is the problem with the realm, it restricts team building with its own characters way too much.", "timestamp": "2026-05-15T10:51:20.053000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2026-05-15T14:29:17.788000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 6}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1504798331593818263", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Please rework how Propagation Caro works", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1181168158678204497", "1361168939622727801", "1181168197425172480", "1361169005435420785"], "is_thread_starter": true}
{"id": "1504858211184939159", "channel_id": "1504798331593818263", "type": 0, "author_id": "1060975277531992145", "author_name": "arandomflamev2", "author_bot": false, "content": "Or please don't release any more units with this kind of Caro variation.", "timestamp": "2026-05-15T14:49:16.460000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❌", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1504798331593818263", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Please rework how Propagation Caro works", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1181168158678204497", "1361168939622727801", "1181168197425172480", "1361169005435420785"]}
